title: Gretchen Whitmer
deleted: Whitmer was elected governor in [[2018 Michigan gubernatorial election|the 2018 gubernatorial election]], defeating Republican [[Attorney General of Michigan|Attorney General]] [[Bill Schuette]]. As governor, Whitmer has focused on healthcare and infrastructure. In February 2020, she was selected to give [[Response to the State of the Union address|the Democratic response]] to [[President of the United States|President]] [[Donald Trump|Donald Trump's]] [[2020 State of the Union Address]].
